This paper is about natural language generation, specifically AMR-to-text generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a neural network model, which involves designing and training a deep learning architecture, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses a benchmark dataset, which involves processing and analyzing data, making it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
